cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. The use of a hierarchical bidirectional LSTM also suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the task of aspect-based sentiment analysis involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the multilingual aspect of the datasets used in the study may also suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
